  "source_id": "hyperthyroidism",
  "name": "Hyperthyroidism - Suppressed TSH Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find hyperthyroid patients via suppressed TSH (<0.1 mIU/L). Includes Path D (subclinical hyperthyroidism without formal dx).",
  "prompt": "Find patients with suppressed TSH results below 0.1 mIU/L.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with suppressed TSH.",
    "broad": "Find patients with thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) measurements below 0.1 mIU/L — indicating hyperthyroidism (normal range 0.4-4.0 mIU/L).",
    "expert": "I need to identify patients with biochemical evidence of hyperthyroidism via a suppressed TSH (thyrotropin) level. Search Observation resources for TSH measurements using the appropriate LOINC code for thyrotropin in serum or plasma, and filter to results where the numeric value falls below the suppressed threshold — a markedly low TSH indicates the pituitary is being inhibited by excess thyroid hormone. This approach captures both overt and subclinical hyperthyroid patients, including those without a formal diagnosis on record."
  },
